Gulf International Signs $1.6 Billion Aluminum Smelter Accord

-- B y   M a s s o u d   A .   D e r h a l l y
-- 
2011-04-29T10:41:47Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-29/gulf-international-signs-1-6-billion-aluminum-smelter-accord.html
Gulf International Investment Group
Holdings Sdn Bhd signed a joint venture agreement with  Aluminum
Corporation of China  Ltd. to develop a $1.6 billion aluminum
smelting plant in Sarawak,  Malaysia .  Smelter Asia Sdn Bhd will develop, own and operate the
aluminum plant, which will have an annual capacity of 370,000
metric tons during the first phase. It’s planned that that
capacity will increase to 700,000 tons, according to an e-mailed
statement from the company.  Gulf International is headed by Malaysian entrepreneur Tan
Sri Syed Mokhtar Al-Bukhary and Mohammed Alabbar, a businessman
based in the United Arab Emirates, who is also the chairman of
 Emaar Properties PJSC (EMAAR) , the U.A.E.’s biggest developer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Massoud A. Derhally in Beirut, Lebanon at   mderhally@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at   barden@bloomberg.net  